04/02/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Acting Parliament Speaker Velimir Simonovic announced early Wednesday (4 February) that an agreement had been reached on the Serbian parliament speaker.
Simonovic is expected to open a plenary session on the matter later in the day.
The democratic parties have been bickering about the speaker and the composition of the cabinet for weeks now.
Vojislav Kostunica's Democratic Party of Serbia implied that talks might be held with the Socialists to elect a speaker.
(B92, BBC, Beta - 04/02/04)
